parentheses clause there, or that little comma clause, like so I'd lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from the evil one. And so as God guides us through life, we're asking God,
please don't put me in positions that tempt me. But knowing He's going to put us in positions
that test us and we may be tempted to fail the test, if that makes sense. So anyway, I think it's,
I think it's a great conversation. I think it's, and I love that we get to unpack it. And when people
go, man, I don't, these seem contradictory. Don't, we love that. So if you've got those, throw them
at us and we'll, we'll unpack and look at them honestly. And you'll hear in our voice, you'll
hear us say, and we can totally sympathize with the fact that this is hard and it's challenging
to us. And that there's passages I don't like, and I don't like that I have to work so hard to
see how they fit in with the whole picture. But we still do. Yeah. There you go. That's great.
Well, Bryn, thank you so much for bringing that up. And then Chris, again, thank you for
engaging with us in that conversation to really bring some light to it.
No, I love it.
Great. Yeah, that's great.
Thank you for joining us for this episode of Reconstructed Faith. If you enjoyed what you
heard or were challenged, please leave us a review. It'll help other people find us.
If you have questions or a topic you'd like to hear discussed, shoot me an email at info
at southspring.org. Reconstructed Faith is a resource of South Spring Baptist Church.
Remember, don't give up. Trust God. Search for answers.
